<seg id=1> China Will Speed Up Construction of the Talent Market System </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, September 1, Telegram.  The Organization Department of the CPC Central Committee and the Ministry of Personnel issued a notice recently urging for reinforcing the talent market construction planning, and speeding up the development of the talent market in order to promote the healthy advancement of the talent market.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> It is pointed out in the notice that the overall objective of the talent market construction and development is to realize independent career choice by individuals, independent talent employment by working units, demand and supply adjustment by the market, improved social services, and complete social security system, making the talent market play a fundamental role in the distribution of talent resources under the macroscopic adjustment and control at the state level.  </seg>
<seg id=4> The near-term objective of the talent market construction and development in the next 2-3 years is to formulate basic policies and regulations needed for the operation of the talent market, to establish talent marketplaces throughout large and medium size cities, to create and develop regional talent information network, to support the advancement of professional talent markets, and to establish regional talent market.  </seg>
<seg id=5> By 2000, an initial talent market system with improved functions, complete operation system, complementary regulations, timely guidance, and good services is about to be established nationwide.  </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Department of the CPC Central Committee and the Ministry of Personnel urged the organization and personnel departments at each level to reinforce the construction and management of the talent market, to strengthen the talent market investigation and planning, to determine the overall arrangement and implementation procedures of the talent market development, and to gradually establish an improved talent market system by taking measures suited to local conditions and exercising classified guidance.  </seg>
</p>
